{{Infobox oil field | name = Pallas gas field | image = | caption = | location_map = Ukraine | location_map_width = | location_map_text = | relief = | coordinates = <!-- {{Coord}} --> | coordinates_ref = | country = [[Ukraine]] | region = [[Black Sea]] | location = | block = | offonshore = Offshore | operators = | partners = [[Naftogaz Ukrainy]] | contractors = | discovery = | start_development = | start_production = | peak_year = | abandonment = | peak_of_production_oil_bbl/d = | peak_of_production_oil_tpy = | peak_of_production_gas_mmcuft/d = | peak_of_production_gas_mmscm/d = | peak_of_production_gas_bcm/y = | oil_production_bbl/d = | oil_production_tpy = | production_year_oil = | production_gas_mmcuft/d = | production_gas_mmscm/d = | production_gas_bcm/y = | production_year_gas = | est_oil_bbl = 3650 | est_oil_t = 490 | recover_oil_bbl = | recover_oil_t = | est_gas_bft = 5495 | est_gas_bcm = 157 | recover_gas_bft = 2625 | recover_gas_bcm = 75 | formations = }} The '''Pallas gas field''' is an offshore [[natural gas field]] located on the [[continental shelf]] of [[Ukraine]] in the north-eastern part of the [[Black Sea]]. It covers area of {{convert|162|km2}}. The estimated 157&nbsp;billion cubic meters of natural gas in place. Recoverable reserves are estimated 75&nbsp;billion cubic meters of natural gas and 490&nbsp;million metric tons of oil.<ref name=kyivpost011210> {{cite news | url= http://www.kyivpost.com/news/business/bus_general/detail/91891/ | title= Gazprom creates two joint ventures with Ukraine | newspaper = [[Kyiv Post]] | agency = Interfax-Ukraine | date=2010-12-01 | accessdate=2010-12-01}} </ref><ref name=rian011210> {{cite news | url= http://en.rian.ru/business/20101201/161582174.html | title= Gazprom to set up 2 joint ventures with Ukraine's Naftogaz | agency = [[RIA Novosti]] | date=2010-12-01 | accessdate=2010-12-01}} </ref>
Originally, the license to explore the Pallas deposit was owned by the Ukrainian company [[Chornomornaftogaz]].<ref name=bbc220107> {{cite news | url= http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-36469947_ITM | title= Ukrainian, Russian firms plan joint gas drilling on Black Sea shelf | agency = [[BBC|BBC Monitoring International Reports]] | date=2007-01-22 | accessdate=2010-12-01 | work=BBC Monitoring International Reports}} </ref> In March 2007, Chornomornaftogaz, [[Naftogaz Ukrainy]], and Russian gas company [[Gazprom]] signed a trilateral protocol on intentions of joint development of the field. In January 2010 the license to develop the gas field was issued by the Ukrainian government to Naftogaz Ukrainy.<ref name=kyivpost140110> {{cite news | url= https://www.kyivpost.com/news/business/bus_general/detail/56971/print/ | title= Cabinet permits Naftogaz to develop Pallas gas field | newspaper = [[Kyiv Post]] | agency = Interfax-Ukraine | date=2010-01-14 | accessdate=2010-12-01}} </ref> On 1 December 2010, Gazprom announced it was agreed to establish a joint venture of Naftogas and Gazprom to develop the Pallas field.<ref name=rian011210/> This was not confirmed by the Ukrainian Fuel and Energy Ministry.<ref name=kyivpost011210/>
