[[Image:Saamelaismuseo.JPG|thumb|250px|Open-Air Museum at Siida]] '''Siida''' is a museum located on [[Lake Inari]] in the village of [[Inari (village)|Inari]] in [[Inari, Finland|Inari]], [[Finland]]. It is home to the Sámi Museum and Northern Lapland Nature Centre. Siida arranges exhibitions on Sámi culture and the nature of Northern Lapland. In addition, Siida has an [[open-air museum]] open in the summers, which was originally known as the Inari Sámi Museum. The first buildings were moved to the museum grounds in 1960. The {{convert|7|ha|adj=on}} area has nearly 50 sites of interest related to Lapland's nature and the Sámi and their culture. Furthermore, the area is where the earliest settlers in Northern Lapland lived and archaeological finds from approximately 9,000 years ago have been found.
